OL,3,CCompany fined #120k after worker
OL,4,Cbreaks leg falling from roof
OL,6,FHSE inspector Sam Applebee said: "EE
OL,7,FRenewables Limited did not properly
OL,8,Fplan this work so it could be carried
OL,9,Fout in a safe manner. There were
OL,10,Finadequate means of protecting the
OL,11,Fworkers from falling off the roof,
OL,12,Fwith the company failing to provide
OL,13,Fedge protection.
OL,15,F"Working at height remains one of the
OL,16,Fbiggest causes of injuries and
OL,17,Ffatalities in Britain, so it is
OL,18,Fimportant that companies ensure they
OL,19,Fimplement the correct control measures
OL,20,Fand safe working practices."
